WEBVTT

00:00.907 --> 00:03.762
- <i>Previously on</i> Lucifer...
- Everything I felt for her

00:03.765 --> 00:05.828
was smoke and mirrors, courtesy of Dad.

00:05.830 --> 00:07.935
DAN: <i>Did you sleep with me
to get intel on this case?</i>

00:07.938 --> 00:09.945
- MOM: <i>Of course.
- What are you doing here?</i>

00:09.948 --> 00:12.726
You don't let your girl go
into enemy territory alone.

00:12.729 --> 00:14.290
The piece is here.

00:14.293 --> 00:16.296
My last words were a clue.

00:16.299 --> 00:17.587
A clue? A clue to what?

00:17.590 --> 00:19.768
Well, you're the one who has
to figure that out, aren't you?

00:19.770 --> 00:20.824
LUCIFER: <i>And you really
think that this is</i>

00:20.826 --> 00:21.963
the Flaming Sword?

00:21.966 --> 00:23.374
It's so not flaming.

00:23.377 --> 00:25.139
That's because only you,

00:25.141 --> 00:28.088
my Lightbringer, can ignite it.

00:28.091 --> 00:30.143
That's it. It's all I've got.

00:30.146 --> 00:32.313
Okay. Then we'll fix it.
There's plenty of time.

00:32.314 --> 00:34.362
MOM: <i>Just not for me.</i>

00:34.365 --> 00:36.722
I do intend to use the Flaming Sword

00:36.725 --> 00:38.144
<i>to cut through the Gates of Heaven.</i>

00:38.147 --> 00:39.179
<i>Once I do that,</i>

00:39.182 --> 00:41.266
I plan on kicking Mom into Heaven

00:41.269 --> 00:43.313
and slamming the gates on her backside.

00:43.316 --> 00:44.540
Won't God destroy her?

00:44.543 --> 00:46.510
Hopefully, they tear each other apart.

00:46.513 --> 00:48.413
Then they'll both get what they deserve.

00:54.603 --> 00:58.072
I'm not the Devil, I'm
just a man who's delusional.

00:58.074 --> 01:02.143
I made it all up. I made it all... up.

01:02.145 --> 01:03.611
(chuckles)

01:05.870 --> 01:07.213
_

01:07.216 --> 01:08.449
I'm doing great.

01:09.518 --> 01:11.118
Great.

01:11.120 --> 01:14.255
Great is... good...

01:14.257 --> 01:16.677
Okay, good talk.

01:16.680 --> 01:17.770
Same time next week?

01:17.773 --> 01:20.741
Uh, sorry, it's just that...

01:20.744 --> 01:22.430
some of the things that you said

01:22.433 --> 01:23.874
in our last session

01:23.877 --> 01:26.829
raised some issues for me.

01:26.832 --> 01:29.451
Do tell. So this secret plan

01:29.454 --> 01:31.133
to cut through the Gates of Heaven...

01:31.136 --> 01:33.615
Well, actually, we've hit
a bit of a snag with that.

01:33.618 --> 01:35.336
The Flaming Sword's kaput.

01:35.339 --> 01:37.410
Now, we can't work out
what's wrong with it,

01:37.413 --> 01:39.714
and until we can, we're in
a bit of a holding pattern.

01:39.716 --> 01:41.862
- Ah, that's a relief.
- Well, why would you say that?

01:41.865 --> 01:44.966
God and His ex having
a fight to the death?

01:44.969 --> 01:47.970
Sounds kind of bad
for, you know, humanity.

01:47.973 --> 01:49.173
Oh, you'll probably be fine.

01:49.176 --> 01:51.209
<i>Probably?</i>

01:51.212 --> 01:52.787
That's not exactly reassuring.

01:52.790 --> 01:55.001
What does Maze think of your plan?

01:55.004 --> 01:56.392
Well, I don't know. I haven't told her.

01:56.394 --> 01:58.431
Hence the secret part
of the secret plan.

01:58.434 --> 02:00.018
- She's your best friend.
- Yes, well,

02:00.021 --> 02:01.521
as much as I love my little sex thug,

02:01.524 --> 02:04.240
Maze can do things that she
thinks are in my best interest

02:04.242 --> 02:07.210
that turn out to be, well, disastrous.

02:07.212 --> 02:08.276
And I can't afford that.

02:08.279 --> 02:10.513
- Hmm.
- But the good news is

02:10.514 --> 02:13.379
she's busy focusing on
her new bestie right now.

02:13.382 --> 02:14.481
The detective.

02:14.484 --> 02:16.851
They're practically inseparable.

02:23.923 --> 02:25.228
Hey, roomie.

02:25.230 --> 02:27.296
- Where you going?
- Maze, hey.

02:27.298 --> 02:29.532
Um, I'm on my way to
work. I'm running late.

02:29.534 --> 02:31.374
Oh, no, but you haven't
had breakfast, come on.

02:33.404 --> 02:35.238
♪ Mm! ♪

02:35.240 --> 02:36.506
No, I'm...

02:36.508 --> 02:38.541
Oh, yeah, no, I'm not hungry.

02:38.543 --> 02:40.376
Yeah, I know, the whole

02:40.378 --> 02:42.531
boring domestic thing... Not my jam.

02:42.534 --> 02:43.534
I should stick to managing

02:43.536 --> 02:45.302
the social part of our friendship.

02:45.305 --> 02:47.383
- You want to kick someone's ass?
- Maze,

02:47.385 --> 02:50.283
I feel like, you know, we've
been hanging out a lot lately.

02:50.286 --> 02:51.287
And I think

02:51.289 --> 02:54.924
perhaps we should expand
our circle of friends.

02:54.926 --> 02:56.392
I got you, Decker.

02:56.394 --> 02:57.527
Yeah? You do?

02:57.529 --> 02:59.896
I smell what you're stepping in.

03:01.131 --> 03:02.465
(snaps fingers) Trust me.

03:02.467 --> 03:05.067
CHLOE: <i>You know, you
should give a Maze a call.</i>

03:05.069 --> 03:06.786
Hasn't it been a while
since you two hung out?

03:06.788 --> 03:08.838
Tired of tripping over
her sex toys, are you?

03:08.840 --> 03:10.139
I didn't say that.

03:10.141 --> 03:12.508
I just think it would
do her, and me, some good

03:12.510 --> 03:14.243
if she wasn't around all the time.

03:14.245 --> 03:16.437
Well, here's the thing.
Maze is like one of those

03:16.440 --> 03:18.673
little baby birds that
imprints on whatever's near.

03:18.676 --> 03:21.083
Sadly, that's you. You are the new me.

03:21.085 --> 03:23.953
I don't want to be you.
I just want some space.

03:23.955 --> 03:26.545
Oh. Eventually Maze will find her place,

03:26.548 --> 03:28.764
but until then, what's the
worst that could happen?

03:28.767 --> 03:30.590
Murder. Confirmed.

03:30.593 --> 03:33.294
Blunt-force trauma to
the back of the head.

03:33.296 --> 03:37.164
The victim got hit with
this backgammon board.

03:37.167 --> 03:38.566
Not very sportsmanlike.

03:38.568 --> 03:41.402
Hmm-mm. He was an orderly.

03:41.404 --> 03:43.371
Toby Mulligan, 32.

03:43.373 --> 03:45.539
- Body was found here.
- Okay.

03:45.541 --> 03:47.274
They interview the staff
or the patients yet?

03:47.276 --> 03:49.810
No, not yet. It's a
psychiatric hospital,

03:49.812 --> 03:51.679
so the staff didn't want
the patients wigging out

03:51.681 --> 03:52.713
over the dead body.

03:52.715 --> 03:54.315
They've been busy moving everyone

03:54.317 --> 03:55.349
to a different floor.

03:55.351 --> 03:57.218
I love the mentally ill.

03:57.220 --> 03:59.587
I mean, who isn't amused by
someone who thinks they're Elvis

03:59.589 --> 04:01.589
or Napoleon or Wesley Snipes?

04:01.591 --> 04:02.690
Who found the body?

04:02.692 --> 04:04.425
- DAN: God.
- Ah! See?!

04:04.427 --> 04:06.508
God Johnson, he's a
patient. He's right in there.

04:06.511 --> 04:08.496
DAN: The guy actually thinks he's God.

04:08.498 --> 04:10.264
He changed his name and everything.

04:10.266 --> 04:11.355
Oh. You two should have

04:11.358 --> 04:12.633
- a lot to talk about.
- Yes.

04:12.635 --> 04:14.602
I would like to have a
chat with the Almighty.

04:14.604 --> 04:16.237
Cool your jets, man, all
right? There's a whole bunch

04:16.238 --> 04:17.982
of bureaucratic hoops to jump through

04:17.985 --> 04:19.140
to set up an interview.

04:19.142 --> 04:21.375
The hospital administrator
has all the info.

04:23.000 --> 04:29.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

04:32.899 --> 04:35.965
Well, hello, God.

04:35.968 --> 04:37.692
Hello, my son.

04:37.694 --> 04:39.160
(laughs, stops short)

04:39.162 --> 04:41.381
Right, yes, I suppose that
would be the standard way

04:41.384 --> 04:43.418
to greet your children.

04:43.421 --> 04:44.448
Nice touch.

04:44.451 --> 04:46.400
What can I do for you?

04:46.402 --> 04:49.136
Well, it's what I can do
for you that's exciting.

04:49.138 --> 04:52.373
See, I can reveal the truth
about the Supreme Being

04:52.375 --> 04:54.041
you've chosen to impersonate.

04:54.043 --> 04:56.043
I bet you wanted to be God because

04:56.045 --> 04:58.546
He's benevolent,
all-powerful, yada yada.

04:58.548 --> 05:02.583
But in actual fact, He's a dick.

05:02.585 --> 05:07.555
Look, if you want to be angry with me,

05:07.557 --> 05:10.224
you just go right on ahead.

05:10.226 --> 05:12.946
I can be anything you need me to be.

05:15.297 --> 05:17.143
Right, enough of this idle chit-chat.

05:17.146 --> 05:20.000
Time to tell you what the
charade's really about.

05:20.002 --> 05:21.425
What do you desire?

05:21.428 --> 05:22.369
Hmm?

05:22.371 --> 05:24.105
To avoid a vengeful ex-wife?

05:24.107 --> 05:26.943
Years of back taxes? What's your game?

05:29.678 --> 05:32.113
Is this a staring contest?

05:32.115 --> 05:34.482
'Cause, you know, I'm
pretty good at those.

05:34.484 --> 05:37.485
How is this possible?

05:37.487 --> 05:39.620
Oh, right, yes, I bet you're on

05:39.622 --> 05:41.489
some really amazing drugs, aren't you?

05:41.491 --> 05:43.390
If so, share-zies.

05:43.392 --> 05:46.327
You're not supposed to be in here.

05:46.329 --> 05:47.628
Oh, never mind.

05:47.630 --> 05:50.531
I'm done with this fraud, anyway.

05:50.533 --> 05:52.366
It was real good seeing you, Samael.

05:53.668 --> 05:55.569
What did you say?

05:59.174 --> 06:00.407
Dad?

06:00.682 --> 06:06.491
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

06:07.797 --> 06:09.910
Has Dad ever visited Earth before?

06:09.911 --> 06:11.378
Not that I'm aware of.

06:11.381 --> 06:13.329
And besides, why would He do so now?

06:13.332 --> 06:15.023
Mm. I don't know, maybe because

06:15.026 --> 06:16.659
we're plotting to overthrow Him.

06:16.662 --> 06:18.829
Even so, Luci, that's
not the way Dad operates.

06:18.832 --> 06:20.249
- (sighs)
- If He has a problem,

06:20.252 --> 06:22.061
He sends an emissary, like me,

06:22.064 --> 06:24.264
or maybe a burning bush.

06:24.266 --> 06:28.134
So how does this God
Johnson know Samael, hmm?

06:28.136 --> 06:29.603
My name.

06:29.605 --> 06:31.738
Oh, wait, I know.

06:31.740 --> 06:33.073
- You do?
- The Internet!

06:33.075 --> 06:35.182
It's truly amazing what
you can find online.

06:35.185 --> 06:36.626
Have you seen that video with the cat

06:36.628 --> 06:37.744
that jumps inside the box?

06:37.746 --> 06:38.979
Very funny, but I didn't even

06:38.981 --> 06:41.198
introduce myself as Lucifer.

06:41.201 --> 06:44.251
And there's something strange about...

06:44.253 --> 06:45.652
I can't explain it.

06:45.654 --> 06:46.987
Because it's just crazy talk

06:46.989 --> 06:48.722
coming from a mentally ill human.

06:50.486 --> 06:52.525
- Well, there might be another reason.
- Right.

06:52.527 --> 06:53.471
What's that?

06:53.474 --> 06:55.127
Well, Earth is His favorite toy.

06:55.130 --> 06:57.597
Maybe He got fed up of
looking at it from afar.

06:57.599 --> 07:00.078
I mean, it's not an
entirely awful place.

07:00.081 --> 07:01.531
Even you have to admit that.

07:01.534 --> 07:04.136
Now you're the one sounding
crazy, Luci, because Earth...

07:04.139 --> 07:06.840
Earth is nothing compared to Heaven.

07:06.842 --> 07:09.360
Oh, come now, brother.

07:09.363 --> 07:11.478
I think you've grown to
like the place, haven't you?

07:11.480 --> 07:13.435
- (scoffs)
- Come on, be honest.

07:13.438 --> 07:15.115
When we return to Heaven,
there must be something

07:15.117 --> 07:16.983
that you're gonna miss, eh?

07:16.985 --> 07:20.521
Or someone, maybe?

07:20.524 --> 07:23.691
Someone in tight leather pants
with a penchant for knives?

07:23.693 --> 07:25.651
I'm referring to Maze, of course.

07:28.864 --> 07:29.864
ELLA: <i>Come on, guys.</i>

07:29.866 --> 07:32.033
Is it really so crazy?

07:32.035 --> 07:34.703
I mean, what if God <i>was</i> one of us?

07:34.706 --> 07:36.738
Just a slob, like one of us.

07:36.740 --> 07:38.006
Exactly. Or just a...

07:38.008 --> 07:39.474
A stranger on a bus.

07:39.476 --> 07:41.442
My father would never
use public transport.

07:41.444 --> 07:42.844
That song is completely unrealistic.

07:42.846 --> 07:44.379
- What song?
- LUCIFER: The song I hate

07:44.381 --> 07:46.080
almost as much as I
hate these hypocrites,

07:46.082 --> 07:47.782
like God Johnson.

07:47.784 --> 07:49.751
Hypocrite? Hmm, I don't know.

07:49.753 --> 07:52.013
I see some similarities
between the two of you.

07:52.016 --> 07:54.118
That man is not my father.

07:54.121 --> 07:56.540
Well, good thing, 'cause
he might be our killer.

07:57.282 --> 07:59.427
<i>Whaaat?</i> Oh, my God,
Ella, how do you know that?

07:59.429 --> 08:01.927
I'll tell you how I know that,
because our victim was bald.

08:01.930 --> 08:04.499
It's very hard to get prints off a body,

08:04.501 --> 08:07.153
so I whipped out the ultraviolet

08:07.156 --> 08:10.123
alternate light source,
and... boom, complete set

08:10.126 --> 08:12.126
on the victim's noggin.

08:12.129 --> 08:13.942
They match one Earl Johnson,

08:13.944 --> 08:16.546
wealthy oil magnate from Odessa, Texas.

08:16.549 --> 08:19.747
Huh. It says here his wife
committed him a few months ago

08:19.749 --> 08:21.616
after he gave all of his money away

08:21.618 --> 08:23.785
and started calling himself "God."

08:23.787 --> 08:27.121
Mr. Johnson never said that
he touched the victim's body.

08:27.123 --> 08:29.359
Left out the killing part as well.

08:29.362 --> 08:31.593
And proving he's the
killer is the perfect way

08:31.595 --> 08:33.870
to expose his false idolatry.

08:33.873 --> 08:34.938
Right, shall we?

08:34.942 --> 08:36.207
No, we shan't.

08:36.210 --> 08:38.527
Because you spoke to
him without permission,

08:38.530 --> 08:40.530
I had to apply for a special hearing

08:40.532 --> 08:41.745
just to interview him.

08:41.748 --> 08:43.200
That'll take at least a few days,

08:43.202 --> 08:44.968
so thank you for that.

08:52.678 --> 08:53.945
Hello, there.

08:53.947 --> 08:55.947
I'd like a suite for
the evening, please.

08:55.949 --> 08:57.082
Preferably one with a view.

08:57.084 --> 08:58.717
Are you joking?

08:58.719 --> 09:00.352
This is a psychiatric hospital.

09:00.354 --> 09:02.220
Apologies, I'm skipping ahead.

09:02.222 --> 09:05.991
Uh, I am the one and
only Lucifer Morningstar.

09:07.360 --> 09:10.662
The Devil. Dark Lord?

09:10.664 --> 09:12.580
Oh, for goodness sake, Beelzebub!

09:13.733 --> 09:15.967
Look, I clearly need to
be committed right away.

09:15.969 --> 09:18.103
Yeah, we're at near capacity, pal.

09:18.105 --> 09:22.207
So unless you're a danger
to yourself or others...

09:22.209 --> 09:23.942
- How's that?
- Great.

09:23.944 --> 09:25.977
Lovely.

09:25.979 --> 09:30.148
♪ I walked into the kitchen ♪

09:30.150 --> 09:33.285
♪ And I said "Hey,
baby, what's cooking?" ♪

09:33.287 --> 09:35.387
Dammit!

09:35.389 --> 09:38.323
♪ Sometimes steak fajitas... ♪

09:38.325 --> 09:39.711
Who stole my pudding again?

09:39.714 --> 09:41.393
Huh?

09:41.395 --> 09:43.061
Markowitz?

09:43.063 --> 09:44.629
Want a taste?

09:48.267 --> 09:50.235
Don't you have better things to do

09:50.237 --> 09:51.403
than to raid our fridge?

09:51.405 --> 09:53.905
I was about to leave
this place altogether,

09:53.907 --> 09:55.740
but I hit an unexpected snag.

09:57.043 --> 09:59.744
Now I need to distract
myself with something.

10:01.147 --> 10:03.381
Hello, something.

10:05.217 --> 10:06.885
You know, just in case I'm giving off an

10:06.887 --> 10:08.920
"I have zero self-respect" vibe,

10:08.922 --> 10:11.256
let me make it clear.

10:11.258 --> 10:12.891
Hands off.

10:12.893 --> 10:13.948
(chuckles)

10:13.951 --> 10:15.323
I'd rather sit at home alone,

10:15.326 --> 10:18.542
and in the dark, than
to hang out with you.

10:23.035 --> 10:25.170
Sassy.

10:25.172 --> 10:26.905
I like it.

10:29.775 --> 10:30.942
Deal me in, gentlemen.

10:30.944 --> 10:32.368
Oh, and lady.

10:32.371 --> 10:34.779
Buy in's ten thousand big ones.

10:34.781 --> 10:37.048
Oh, right, high stakes. I like it.

10:37.050 --> 10:38.049
Pig farts!

10:38.051 --> 10:39.784
Crash and burn.

10:39.786 --> 10:41.319
Oh, I see, you're one of those. Right.

10:41.321 --> 10:43.054
- 200.
- MAN: I swear,

10:43.056 --> 10:46.725
I am gonna stab you in
the eye if you do not stop

10:46.727 --> 10:47.926
dealing me crap!

10:48.734 --> 10:49.601
Call.

10:49.604 --> 10:50.603
I'm out.

10:50.606 --> 10:53.731
Um, ten thousand, all in.

10:53.734 --> 10:56.101
- (grunts)
- Fold.

10:58.270 --> 11:00.739
What do you know about God Johnson?

11:00.741 --> 11:02.240
I like fire.

11:02.242 --> 11:03.348
Right, never mind.

11:03.351 --> 11:04.950
Maybe I can help.

11:04.953 --> 11:08.262
- I did see him perform a miracle.
- Really?

11:09.949 --> 11:12.050
He scored me an extra
Jell-O at snack time.

11:12.052 --> 11:13.418
Shh.

11:13.420 --> 11:15.320
Useless.

11:15.322 --> 11:17.022
Royal flush.

11:17.024 --> 11:18.812
- Cheater!
- Red pubic hair!

11:18.815 --> 11:19.814
Mm-hmm.

11:21.127 --> 11:22.761
DOCTOR: Billy, what did I tell you

11:22.763 --> 11:24.929
about throwing your underwear?

11:24.931 --> 11:26.031
They're not mine.

11:26.033 --> 11:27.438
DOCTOR: Really? 'Cause you're naked.

11:27.440 --> 11:29.868
Yes, I'm more of a boxer
briefs guy, but thank you.

11:29.870 --> 11:31.770
Sorry about that. You must be Lucifer.

11:31.772 --> 11:32.937
I'm Dr. Garrity.

11:32.939 --> 11:34.039
Oh. Yes.

11:34.041 --> 11:35.173
Can we talk later?

11:35.175 --> 11:37.442
I have to get him to his
electroshock treatment.

11:37.444 --> 11:38.410
Really?

11:38.412 --> 11:40.245
- Just kidding.
- Yes.

11:40.247 --> 11:41.913
You, this way. Come.

11:41.915 --> 11:43.782
- Very good.
- Let's go find you some pants.

11:46.318 --> 11:47.318
Dad.

11:50.923 --> 11:52.057
(sighs)

12:00.593 --> 12:03.428
Aha! Of course, you're the murderer.

12:04.236 --> 12:05.904
Right, suppose I should thwart you now.

12:05.906 --> 12:09.121
Off to jail, cowboy.

12:11.110 --> 12:12.844
No, please, I have to save her.

12:12.846 --> 12:13.978
What do you mean, save her?

12:17.832 --> 12:19.117
(exhales)

12:27.827 --> 12:30.662
- (grunts)
- (gasps)

12:40.247 --> 12:42.115
It really is you.

12:44.808 --> 12:47.443
You son of a bitch.

12:49.933 --> 12:51.996
Why the hell would you
get yourself committed?

12:51.998 --> 12:54.966
I did it to help the investigation.

12:54.968 --> 12:56.867
Hey.

12:56.869 --> 12:58.135
What do you think?

12:58.137 --> 12:59.370
It's a good likeness, isn't it?

12:59.372 --> 13:01.005
That's it, I'm pulling the plug.

13:01.007 --> 13:02.373
- I'm getting you out of here, now.
- No, no, no, no.

13:02.375 --> 13:03.774
You were the one who
said it would be difficult

13:03.776 --> 13:05.268
to interview God Johnson.

13:05.271 --> 13:06.410
So, I took some initiative.

13:06.412 --> 13:08.012
I went undercover.

13:08.015 --> 13:10.659
You must admit having an inside
man could be quite effective.

13:10.662 --> 13:11.716
