Tell me what?

27:25.281 --> 27:27.416
We're all going back to Heaven.

27:33.923 --> 27:37.359
So tell me, how, how do you
have your job and stay sane?

27:37.361 --> 27:38.756
(exhaling): Oh, uh...

27:38.759 --> 27:40.529
Years of practice, um...

27:40.531 --> 27:42.498
Drugs. Mostly drugs.

27:42.500 --> 27:43.982
Mm. (laughs)

27:43.985 --> 27:45.834
But, um, but, seriously, um, I just...

27:45.836 --> 27:47.308
I try and see beneath the DSM.

27:47.311 --> 27:49.705
Try to remember that each
one of them is a person.

27:49.707 --> 27:53.709
Yeah. I, uh, I saw this
older gentleman the other day.

27:53.711 --> 27:56.316
Uh, long white hair. White beard.

27:56.319 --> 27:58.052
He reminded me of my crazy Uncle Al.

27:58.055 --> 28:00.381
- You must be talking about Dale.
- Yeah, what's his deal?

28:00.384 --> 28:02.784
Is he one of the violent ones?

28:04.754 --> 28:05.821
Um...

28:05.823 --> 28:07.256
Uh...

28:07.258 --> 28:11.419
Um, what kind of civil
servant are you, exactly?

28:11.422 --> 28:12.528
(phone chimes)

28:14.264 --> 28:18.200
Wow. Well, this evening just
got even more interesting.

28:18.202 --> 28:20.536
Apparently, your co-worker,
Lucifer, just escaped

28:20.538 --> 28:23.272
and took God Johnson with him.

28:29.469 --> 28:31.369
What's he doing here, Lucifer?

28:31.372 --> 28:33.323
I don't know. You married him.

28:33.325 --> 28:35.792
Well, it kind of ruins our plans
to storm the Gates of Heaven

28:35.794 --> 28:37.327
and destroy him.

28:37.329 --> 28:39.829
Well, I'm thinking we might
not need to do that anymore.

28:39.831 --> 28:42.799
I will never forgive him, if
that's what you're getting at.

28:42.801 --> 28:44.134
The point is, Mum,

28:44.136 --> 28:48.671
that I think Dad...
sincerely misses you.

28:48.673 --> 28:50.140
(scoffs)

28:50.142 --> 28:52.075
Well, of course I do. How could I not?

28:52.077 --> 28:53.977
Look at you.

28:55.012 --> 28:57.847
An absolute vision.

28:57.849 --> 28:59.582
Glowing, even now.

28:59.584 --> 29:02.652
Oh, you have no idea. (laughs softly)

29:02.654 --> 29:04.687
I'm just gonna... Doctor.

29:04.689 --> 29:07.690
For the life of me, I can't even
remember why we were fighting.

29:07.692 --> 29:09.692
The flames? Eternal damnation?

29:09.694 --> 29:11.594
The... Kind of hard to forget.

29:11.596 --> 29:14.764
JOHNSON: I am so sorry
that you suffered.

29:14.766 --> 29:17.867
Well, I su... suppose I should apologize

29:17.869 --> 29:20.703
for trying to destroy your precious toy

29:20.705 --> 29:24.007
with floods and with
plagues and whatnot.

29:24.009 --> 29:26.876
I guess humanity isn't entirely awful.

29:26.878 --> 29:29.145
They did make vodka.

29:29.147 --> 29:30.713
Roller coasters.

29:30.715 --> 29:32.257
Triple crème Brie.

29:33.984 --> 29:35.985
You hear about dancing?

29:35.987 --> 29:39.022
Yes, I actually did some
of that on a table, once.

29:39.024 --> 29:42.258
("Can't Take My Eyes Off
Of You" begins playing)

29:45.329 --> 29:47.230
Would you do me this honor?

29:53.804 --> 29:57.640
♪ You're just too good to be true ♪

29:57.642 --> 30:01.244
♪ Can't take my eyes off of you ♪

30:01.246 --> 30:06.049
♪ You'd be like heaven to touch... ♪

30:06.051 --> 30:09.719
You sure it's revenge you're after?

30:09.721 --> 30:12.155
Of course it is. What else would it be?

30:12.157 --> 30:17.026
♪ And I'm so glad I'm alive ♪

30:17.028 --> 30:20.897
♪ You're just too good to be true ♪

30:20.899 --> 30:22.999
What's the matter?

30:23.001 --> 30:24.767
This.

30:24.769 --> 30:26.436
I didn't think this was possible.

30:26.438 --> 30:28.238
It wasn't part of the plan.

30:28.240 --> 30:30.807
So, maybe...

30:30.809 --> 30:33.810
maybe we make a new plan.

30:33.812 --> 30:36.012
This time, we make it together.

30:37.882 --> 30:40.617
♪ I love you, baby ♪

30:40.619 --> 30:42.185
♪ And if it's quite all right ♪

30:42.187 --> 30:44.120
♪ I need you, baby ♪

30:44.122 --> 30:46.411
♪ To warm the lonely nights ♪

30:46.414 --> 30:48.658
♪ I love you, baby ♪

30:48.660 --> 30:50.618
- ♪ Trust in me when I say ♪
- (door opens)

30:50.621 --> 30:52.395
Lucifer!

30:52.397 --> 30:54.397
Detective!

30:54.399 --> 30:56.266
Seriously?

30:56.268 --> 30:58.134
♪ Don't bring me down, I pray ♪

30:58.136 --> 30:59.269
♪ Oh, pretty baby ♪

30:59.271 --> 31:00.670
Okay, outside now.

31:00.672 --> 31:02.010
♪ Now that I've found you stay ♪

31:02.013 --> 31:04.948
♪ And let me love you. ♪

31:04.951 --> 31:06.526
CHLOE: First you check yourself

31:06.529 --> 31:08.010
into a mental hospital,

31:08.013 --> 31:11.047
only to kidnap another
patient and escape.

31:11.049 --> 31:13.283
Lucifer, how is that helping?

31:13.285 --> 31:15.885
Well, i-if you must know,

31:15.887 --> 31:18.154
God Johnson is indeed my father,

31:18.156 --> 31:20.790
and, uh, I needed to
do a little matchmaking.

31:20.792 --> 31:22.358
(sighs)

31:22.360 --> 31:24.427
With him and Charlotte Richards?

31:24.429 --> 31:27.096
I mean, I'm scared to know
how she ties into all this.

31:27.098 --> 31:29.832
Well, never mind that.
What about our killer?

31:29.834 --> 31:32.001
Hmm? Did you find proof of Santa Claus?

31:32.003 --> 31:33.036
Time for your meds.

31:33.038 --> 31:34.370
Ooh, lovely.

31:34.372 --> 31:37.106
Thank you. Right.

31:37.108 --> 31:39.108
Unexpected perk of the place. (chuckles)

31:39.110 --> 31:40.410
Maybe it's a good thing

31:40.412 --> 31:43.653
there's another day on
your 72-hour hold. You know?

31:43.656 --> 31:45.915
Maybe being here is the
best thing for you right now.

31:45.917 --> 31:47.116
Okay.

31:52.042 --> 31:55.158
(knocking on door)

31:55.160 --> 31:56.392
Hey.

31:56.394 --> 31:58.222
I just wanted to say

31:58.225 --> 32:01.064
that I'm sorry I lied.

32:01.066 --> 32:04.867
I, um...

32:04.869 --> 32:06.736
Sometimes with work,

32:06.738 --> 32:08.137
I get shortsighted.

32:08.139 --> 32:10.273
And I never wanted to...

32:10.275 --> 32:11.274
Use me?

32:13.310 --> 32:15.278
(quietly): Yeah.

32:17.214 --> 32:20.116
If you had just been up-front with me,

32:20.118 --> 32:22.919
I would've told you that Dale,
the guy you were asking about,

32:22.921 --> 32:24.320
he's been here for 15 years.

32:24.322 --> 32:28.958
Yeah, he can seem a bit
prickly, but he's a teddy bear.

32:28.960 --> 32:30.860
He's got no violent tendencies.

32:30.862 --> 32:33.390
There is just no way he'd kill someone.

32:33.393 --> 32:34.659
All right.

32:34.662 --> 32:39.268
Legally, I can't let you
look at Dale's medical file.

32:39.270 --> 32:42.038
But, um...

32:42.040 --> 32:45.041
what happens when I turn away is, um,

32:45.043 --> 32:46.042
out of my hands.

32:46.044 --> 32:48.711
Thank you.

32:48.713 --> 32:50.947
(quietly): Yeah.

32:50.949 --> 32:54.984
Ooh, look, a Nigerian
prince needs my help.

32:54.986 --> 32:56.986
Wow.

32:56.988 --> 32:58.788
Thanks.

33:03.193 --> 33:04.861
Santa Claus?

33:05.847 --> 33:07.397
Okay, so what's the big deal?

33:07.399 --> 33:08.731
Someone dresses up as Santa every year.

33:08.733 --> 33:09.518
Patients love it.

33:09.521 --> 33:11.067
Yeah, well, that someone
could be the killer.

33:11.069 --> 33:12.201
But a different person
does it every year.

33:12.203 --> 33:14.170
Even I did it a few years back.

33:14.172 --> 33:17.106
Okay, we store the, uh, costume in here.

33:19.743 --> 33:21.711
Wait, wait, wait.

33:21.713 --> 33:23.212
(clears throat)

33:30.954 --> 33:32.855
Where's the beard? The red hat?

33:32.857 --> 33:34.824
- It should be in there.
- Okay, two things.

33:34.826 --> 33:38.227
Who else has a key to
that cabinet? And...

33:38.229 --> 33:40.129
I need you to put these on.

33:40.131 --> 33:42.598
Ooh, ooh.

33:42.600 --> 33:45.368
These drugs are a bit
different, aren't they?

33:45.370 --> 33:48.704
'Cause I can't feel my tongue.

33:48.706 --> 33:51.841
Oh. Hello, pretty kitty,

33:51.843 --> 33:54.677
kitty, kitty, kitty...

33:54.679 --> 33:58.047
Santa, you're here as well?

33:58.049 --> 34:00.716
Oh, I'm afraid I've been a naughty boy.

34:00.718 --> 34:01.845
(grunts)

34:07.353 --> 34:10.197
You see, I am actually the Devil.

34:10.201 --> 34:12.101
(distorted): No, you're not the Devil.

34:12.103 --> 34:14.771
You're just a man who's
delusional in a mental hospital.

34:14.773 --> 34:16.639
You made it all up.

34:16.641 --> 34:17.706
So...

34:18.742 --> 34:20.510
I'm not the Devil.

34:20.512 --> 34:23.212
I'm just a man who's delusional.

34:23.214 --> 34:24.480
I made it all up.

34:24.482 --> 34:26.949
I made it all up!

34:26.951 --> 34:31.187
I made it all up. (chuckles)

34:31.188 --> 34:33.723
Hello, son.

34:33.725 --> 34:34.891
Dad!

34:34.893 --> 34:37.310
See? I am the Devil.

34:37.313 --> 34:39.228
Nice try, Santa.

34:39.230 --> 34:40.279
(chuckles)

34:40.282 --> 34:43.208
- Tell me what you told the police.
- Only the truth.

34:43.212 --> 34:47.292
That you, Mr. Kringle,
are a cold-blooded killer.

34:47.295 --> 34:50.018
- What else?
- What do you want to know, Nurse Kipsy?

34:59.585 --> 35:01.385
Why aren't the drugs working on you?

35:01.387 --> 35:02.687
Well, it's obvious, isn't it?

35:02.689 --> 35:04.930
It's because he's God!

35:04.957 --> 35:06.490
LUCIFER: Uh, oh.

35:06.492 --> 35:07.825
Hey.

35:07.827 --> 35:09.393
Hey, they shouldn't be working

35:09.395 --> 35:11.262
on me, either, but...

35:11.264 --> 35:12.663
Is the detective still here?

35:12.665 --> 35:14.699
- That might explain it.
- Shut up.

35:14.701 --> 35:16.500
- Okay.
- KIPSY: Doesn't matter.

35:16.502 --> 35:18.769
Now you know it's me,
I have to kill you both.

35:18.771 --> 35:21.305
(sighs)

35:23.842 --> 35:24.976
What's that for?

35:24.978 --> 35:26.410
A long shot.

35:35.320 --> 35:36.887
Okay.

35:36.889 --> 35:39.223
(camera clicks)

35:39.225 --> 35:41.459
That's got to be the
coolest thing I've ever seen.

35:41.461 --> 35:43.928
I'd-I'd applaud, you
know, if I weren't cuffed.

35:43.930 --> 35:45.930
Sorry about that.
It's just a precaution.

35:45.932 --> 35:47.465
- Hey, I get it.
- (cell phone beeps)

35:47.467 --> 35:49.000
- Bingo.
- Wow.

35:49.002 --> 35:50.267
That was fast.

35:50.269 --> 35:51.502
Yeah, you don't know Ella.

35:51.504 --> 35:54.338
The print belongs to
one Patricia Hightower.

35:54.340 --> 35:55.873
We have a patient named Sue Hightower,

35:55.875 --> 35:57.408
the one God Johnson attacked.

35:57.410 --> 36:00.511
Okay. I'm waiting on a DMV photo.

36:00.513 --> 36:01.746
(cell phone beeps)

36:01.748 --> 36:03.188
She looks familiar.

36:04.383 --> 36:05.683
That's Nurse Kipsy.

36:05.685 --> 36:07.485
KIPSY: <i>I changed my name</i>

36:07.487 --> 36:09.350
so no one would know she's my mother.

36:11.390 --> 36:15.960
She was a raging bitch my entire life.

36:15.962 --> 36:19.897
Controlling, manipulative...

36:19.899 --> 36:22.731
She tortured me.

36:22.734 --> 36:25.582
So I decided to torture her.

36:25.585 --> 36:27.571
Pumped her full of
drugs, drove her crazy.

36:27.573 --> 36:29.573
Preaching to the choir, sister.

36:29.575 --> 36:30.841
Evil parents

36:30.843 --> 36:32.276
deserve to be punished.

36:32.278 --> 36:35.212
You had every right to destroy her.

36:36.381 --> 36:37.581
But what about the orderly?

36:37.583 --> 36:39.583
He found out what I was doing.

36:39.585 --> 36:41.318
He... said he was gonna turn me in.

36:41.320 --> 36:42.319
I had no choice.

36:42.321 --> 36:43.854
No, he was innocent

36:43.856 --> 36:45.304
and you killed him,

36:45.307 --> 36:48.288
so I am gonna have to punish you.

36:48.291 --> 36:50.692
(grunts)

36:52.228 --> 36:54.229
Why aren't I pulverizing you?

36:54.232 --> 36:57.566
Uh, one because you're a nutjob.

36:57.568 --> 36:58.901
And two,

36:58.903 --> 37:00.870
because I switched out your normal meds

37:00.872 --> 37:02.838
with a massive dose of Haldol.

37:02.840 --> 37:03.973
(chuckles)

37:03.975 --> 37:05.741
You know...

37:07.353 --> 37:08.253
they don't normally

37:08.256 --> 37:09.745
let patients wear belts.

37:09.747 --> 37:12.014
Suicide risk.

37:12.016 --> 37:14.864
So, thank you for getting a
special dispensation for yours

37:14.867 --> 37:16.942
because now I got it.

37:16.945 --> 37:19.255
God is gonna kill Lucifer,

37:19.257 --> 37:20.690
then hang himself.

37:21.692 --> 37:23.059
(chuckles)

37:23.061 --> 37:25.928
Kind of poetic, don't you think?

37:25.930 --> 37:27.863
Gonna go find a ladder.

37:27.865 --> 37:29.932
Oh, a ladder. (chuckles)

37:29.934 --> 37:31.067
JOHNSON: Now, I had no idea

37:31.069 --> 37:33.469
you were so angry with me.

37:33.471 --> 37:35.171
Really?

37:35.173 --> 37:38.249
'Cause I... I've been
pretty up-front about it.

37:38.252 --> 37:40.676
But to want to destroy me?

37:40.678 --> 37:42.878
That's pretty serious.

37:42.880 --> 37:44.947
You mind telling me why?

37:44.949 --> 37:48.084
Because...

37:48.086 --> 37:50.820
because I'm your son.

37:50.822 --> 37:53.089
And...

37:55.125 --> 37:56.826
you rejected me.

37:57.828 --> 37:59.695
Oh.

38:01.498 --> 38:03.966
Well, then I guess I
can't say as I blame you.

38:03.968 --> 38:05.822
Fact of the matter is,

38:05.825 --> 38:07.124
I don't even remember why

38:07.127 --> 38:08.807
I was ever so angry
with you to begin with.

38:11.372 --> 38:15.021
For what it's worth...

38:15.023 --> 38:17.858
I am sorry.

38:17.860 --> 38:20.427
I truly am.

38:20.429 --> 38:23.830
And I am proud of you, Samael.

38:23.832 --> 38:25.832
I am proud of the man you've become.

38:28.970 --> 38:30.704
So, what do you say...

38:30.706 --> 38:32.105
Wait, no.

38:32.107 --> 38:33.340
Not... not my belt.

38:33.342 --> 38:34.608
You can't take my belt. It's mine.

38:34.610 --> 38:37.005
Patricia Hightower, LAPD. Don't move.

38:37.008 --> 38:38.845
(belt clatters on floor)

38:38.847 --> 38:41.815
Detective. (whoops)

38:41.817 --> 38:43.450
You okay?

38:43.452 --> 38:44.785
Honestly...

38:44.787 --> 38:47.125
I've never felt better.

38:47.889 --> 38:51.049
(grunts)

38:51.052 --> 38:53.586
What this? What-What just happened?

38:53.589 --> 38:56.323
What are you talking
about? We just beat Santa.

38:56.998 --> 38:58.498
Who are you?

38:58.500 --> 38:59.599
It's me, Dad.

38:59.601 --> 39:01.468
Lucifer.

39:01.470 --> 39:04.078
Does someone want to tell
me what the hell is going on?

39:04.081 --> 39:06.181
Get me out of these damn things.

39:15.226 --> 39:17.060
"The piece is here."

39:24.759 --> 39:26.026
(scoffs)

39:26.028 --> 39:28.094
Well, what do you know.

39:28.096 --> 39:29.713
It fits perfectly.

39:29.716 --> 39:32.383
Yes, I think this is what
Uriel was trying to tell me.

39:33.634 --> 39:35.769
Just before he died,

39:35.771 --> 39:38.505
he whispered in my ear,
"The piece is here."

39:38.507 --> 39:40.674
I mean, I thought it
was nonsense, but...

39:40.676 --> 39:42.542
this must be why the
sword wasn't working.

39:42.544 --> 39:43.777
It wasn't complete.

39:43.779 --> 39:45.512
Dad supposedly destroyed
the Flaming Sword

39:45.514 --> 39:46.580
after the rebellion.

39:46.582 --> 39:48.114
So, are you saying

39:48.116 --> 39:50.700
he just broke it into two
pieces? Azrael's blade...

39:50.703 --> 39:51.418
And this.

39:51.420 --> 39:54.087
Yes, which somehow ended up on Earth.

39:54.089 --> 39:55.989
Its power probably awakened

39:55.991 --> 39:59.646
when Azrael's blade ended up here, too.

39:59.660 --> 40:01.995
Which is when Mr. Johnson
must've stumbled upon it.

40:01.997 --> 40:03.768
But why did he think he was father?

40:03.771 --> 40:07.200
Well, I mean, Azrael's
blade inspired death.

40:07.202 --> 40:10.871
Maybe this piece activated
the opposite... life.

40:10.873 --> 40:12.902
Healing. Gave him the power

40:12.905 --> 40:14.371
and knowledge of the divine.

40:14.374 --> 40:17.209
And when he found out that
he could heal like that, he...

40:17.211 --> 40:18.443
he thought he was God.

40:18.445 --> 40:19.978
What's more important is that

40:19.980 --> 40:23.048
now the sword's complete,
we can get on with our plan.

40:23.050 --> 40:25.383
So... the...

40:25.385 --> 40:27.219
(sighs)

40:27.221 --> 40:29.888
Or not.

40:34.827 --> 40:36.762
Maybe there's another piece missing.

40:36.764 --> 40:39.185
Or maybe a dragon has to breathe on it.

40:39.188 --> 40:40.282
Who knows?

40:40.285 --> 40:41.900
Well, maybe Mum does.

40:41.902 --> 40:43.769
Did...

40:43.771 --> 40:45.403
Where is she, anyway?

40:45.405 --> 40:47.839
<i>(knock on door)</i>

40:53.980 --> 40:56.179
I thought I made myself clear.

40:56.182 --> 40:58.049
I kissed a man today.

40:58.051 --> 40:59.684
What's your deal?

40:59.686 --> 41:02.020
I thought he was my ex-husband.

41:02.022 --> 41:04.289
When I kissed him,

41:04.291 --> 41:07.225
I realized it wasn't him.

41:07.227 --> 41:09.327
And the strangest part is,

41:09.329 --> 41:12.197
I don't know what's more upsetting...

41:12.199 --> 41:14.866
that it wasn't him? (chuckles)

41:17.692 --> 41:20.583
Or that I... I wished it was.

41:20.586 --> 41:21.973
Wow.

41:21.975 --> 41:24.176
I just don't want to be alone.

41:24.178 --> 41:27.879
Could we just hold each other?

41:27.881 --> 41:31.249
Please?

41:35.288 --> 41:37.155
With your pants off, of course.

41:45.932 --> 41:48.633
I still can't believe I
gave all my money away.

41:48.635 --> 41:50.268
Well, if it's any consolation,

41:50.270 --> 41:53.171
- you haven't exactly been yourself of late.
- Yeah.

41:53.173 --> 41:54.940
Listen, I wanted to ask you...

41:54.942 --> 41:57.248
what's the last thing you remember?

41:57.251 --> 41:59.678
I was in New Mexico for work,

41:59.680 --> 42:02.047
I was walking through
this Navajo gift shop.

42:02.049 --> 42:05.417
I saw a cool belt buckle,
so I picked it up, and...

42:05.419 --> 42:07.202
next thing I knew, I woke up

42:07.205 --> 42:08.605
strapped to a gurney next to you.

42:08.608 --> 42:10.288
- Lucky you.
- Yeah.

42:10.290 --> 42:12.123
Hey, they, uh,

42:12.125 --> 42:13.391
they say we was arguing.

42:13.393 --> 42:16.895
If I did or said something
to upset you, I apologize.

42:16.897 --> 42:20.231
No, no, you were quite lovely actually.

42:21.366 --> 42:24.835
For a brief moment, I
thought you were my father.

42:24.838 --> 42:26.137
(chuckles)

42:26.139 --> 42:29.007
A man for whom I harbor a
great deal of resentment.

42:29.009 --> 42:31.412
And you said some things

42:31.415 --> 42:34.279
that I think I wish
he'd always said to me,

42:34.281 --> 42:37.115
so for that I thank you.

42:37.117 --> 42:40.387
Well, I guess even a blind squirrel

42:40.390 --> 42:41.710
catches a nut every now and then.

